     2)&nbsp;Most people who have shopped online have come across a hashing algorithm without even realizing it. When a site brags about protecting data through 256 bit encryption, the site is using a hashing algorithm to protect data. For marketing reasons, though, "256 bit encryption" sounds a lot better than "hashing algorithm," though. 
     These algorithms are great at keeping data safe provided that some criminal doesn't get his mitts on the key to unlock the algorithm and read that data. The data, then, is only safe if the algorithm is protected. 
